cat << EOF
e2fsprogs - The EXT file system utilities and libraries. EXT stands for
"Extended Filesystem". It is the main filesystem type used for hard disks on
Debian and other Linux systems. This package contains programs for creating,
checking, and maintaining EXT filesystems, and the generic fsck wrapper.
The ext2fsprogs package contains essential EXT filesystem utilities which
consists of e2fsck,

mke2fs, debugfs, dumpe2fs, tune2fs, and most of the other core EXT filesystem
utilities.

This module also provides the generic init.d mount script which is vital to
your linux system.
EOF
